12:06.560 --> 12:09.280
Wait, you really forced your students to watch me?

12:09.280 --> 12:10.320
It's true.

12:10.320 --> 12:16.160
Anyway, in progress and poverty, George argued that a single land value tax was needed

12:16.160 --> 12:23.920
because most of the wealth created by social and technological advances in an industrial free market economy

12:23.920 --> 12:26.720
was actually owned by landowners.

12:26.720 --> 12:33.760
And many of those landowners had monopolies over markets through something called economic rent.

12:33.760 --> 12:39.040
Economic rent is basically income gained from controlling a limited resource.

12:39.040 --> 12:45.520
So even though these landowners did nothing to improve the land value, they still got the profit.

12:45.520 --> 12:49.600
And remember, this was land, a natural resource.

12:49.600 --> 12:51.040
It was there already.

12:51.040 --> 12:53.120
These landowners didn't create it.

12:53.120 --> 12:58.960
They were just benefiting from something they did nothing to help create, nor improve.

12:58.960 --> 13:03.040
In progress and poverty, George argued the game was rigged.

13:03.040 --> 13:08.480
And the only way to fix the game was not to tax the worker on what they earn

13:08.480 --> 13:11.600
because that would disincentivize them from working

13:11.600 --> 13:17.040
and not to tax the owner of capital through taxes on what they own or buy

13:17.040 --> 13:21.520
because that would disincentivize them from investing.

13:21.520 --> 13:27.280
To George, land was common property and everyone was entitled to it.

13:27.840 --> 13:30.160
But that doesn't mean he was a Marxist, though.

13:30.160 --> 13:30.720
Oh, no.

13:32.000 --> 13:33.840
George was a Georgist.

13:33.840 --> 13:36.240
George was fine with capitalism.

13:36.240 --> 13:42.800
He just wasn't a fan of rigged capitalism in which the landowners were essentially parasites.

13:42.800 --> 13:47.360
Because he thought everyone was entitled to the land, many of George's followers

13:47.360 --> 13:51.760
hesitated to even call a land value tax a tax.

13:51.760 --> 13:57.920
They preferred to call it basically rent paid to society in exchange for getting to

13:57.920 --> 14:03.440
exclusively use the land for whatever they wanted, while also compensating for the fact

14:03.440 --> 14:05.840
that others couldn't use it.

14:05.920 --> 14:11.200
By the way, uh, yeah, George's followers soon became known as Georgeus

14:11.200 --> 14:16.000
and George's whole economic ideology became known as Georgeism.

14:16.000 --> 14:22.880
Anyway, George's book and ideas became so popular that governments around the world

14:22.880 --> 14:24.160
got rid of all taxes.

14:24.960 --> 14:30.400
And that's why today we only have a land use tax.

14:30.400 --> 14:32.480
And we all lived happily ever after.

