You see, people who owned land, and this may be a bit surprising to you,

15:06.320 --> 15:08.960
didn't like the idea of a land value tax.

15:08.960 --> 15:10.240
Go figure, huh?

15:10.240 --> 15:16.000
Many people liked the fact that they could just let land sit there and it would automatically

15:16.000 --> 15:16.880
go up in value.

15:16.880 --> 15:24.080
In 1886, Henry once again gave politics an old try when he was recruited by the United

15:24.080 --> 15:27.520
Labor Party to run for mayor of New York City.

15:27.520 --> 15:33.040
However, he was up against the machine, aka the establishment.

15:33.680 --> 15:39.040
Okay, Tammany Hall, the powerful political organization that essentially controlled

15:39.040 --> 15:40.800
New York politics.

15:40.800 --> 15:46.000
Tammany Hall feared that if George won the election, politics in the city might be

15:46.000 --> 15:53.040
reorganized along class lines instead of ethnic lines, which is where Tammany got its power.

15:53.040 --> 15:59.360
Tammany Hall called George's supporters, quote, anarchists, nihilists, communists,

15:59.360 --> 16:01.040
and socialists.

16:01.040 --> 16:06.480
Well, George lost the election, but he surprised many with a strong second place finish.

16:06.480 --> 16:11.920
Not only that, but there is some evidence that voter fraud may have been involved.

16:13.120 --> 16:14.480
Just saying.

16:14.480 --> 16:18.640
His supporters were not even allowed to oversee the ballot count.

16:18.640 --> 16:24.640
Regardless, he did finish ahead of an obscure dude by the name of Theodore Roosevelt, and

16:24.640 --> 16:31.040
despite losing the election for the rest of his life, George's popularity only continued to grow.

16:31.040 --> 16:37.760
In 1897, he ran for mayor of New York City again, but just four days before the election,

16:37.760 --> 16:41.040
he suffered a fatal stroke that shocked the nation.

16:41.040 --> 16:47.760
His death made international headlines, and possibly as many as 200,000 people showed up

16:47.760 --> 16:49.280
to view his body.

16:49.280 --> 16:55.520
At the time of his death, Henry George was the most well-known economist around, and

16:55.520 --> 16:58.640
Georgism was arguably at its peak.

16:58.640 --> 17:03.760
And yet, I only learned about George and Georgism like three years ago.

17:03.760 --> 17:10.000
And as I researched for this video, I noticed that the man and his land value tax idea are

17:10.000 --> 17:12.640
more obscure than goat cheese on pizza.

17:12.640 --> 17:13.440
Why is that?

17:14.880 --> 17:17.360
Why did Georgism go out of style?

17:17.360 --> 17:20.080
Why did Georgism go out of style, huh?

17:20.080 --> 17:25.200
Well, first of all, in his later years, George was too much of a purist.

17:25.200 --> 17:30.000
He often refused to compromise on his ideals with other progressive reformers.

17:30.000 --> 17:34.480
Other progressive reformers didn't like how he was still okay with almost all capital,

17:34.480 --> 17:38.960
uh, existing, and how he rejected a strong role for government.

17:38.960 --> 17:43.120
They didn't like his opposition to public ownership of certain types of infrastructure,

17:43.120 --> 17:48.640
his support of free trade, and him being a gradualist versus trying to start a radical

17:48.640 --> 17:49.440
revolution.

17:49.440 --> 17:55.040
Overall, he frustrated fellow progressive reformers by not shutting up about a land

17:55.040 --> 17:59.760
value tax, thinking that was the only thing that could solve everybody's problems.

17:59.760 --> 18:04.400
But of course, there were also the landowners, and the speculators.

18:04.400 --> 18:09.200
Even today, much wealth is earned through owning land.

18:09.200 --> 18:12.560
And a land value tax threatens that.

18:12.560 --> 18:18.560
But more importantly, land speculators have tremendous power over the government and the

18:19.200 --> 18:23.600
media, and they would simply not get to make money anymore with a land value tax.

18:23.600 --> 18:28.560
Now, there are other reasons why Georgism faded out in the 1900s.

18:28.560 --> 18:31.920
World War I really hurt its momentum for starters.

18:31.920 --> 18:38.560
Another big thing that is probably not brought up enough by Georgia is that cars got way more

18:38.560 --> 18:44.560
popular during the century so that people could more easily travel longer distances to

18:44.560 --> 18:45.920
get to their land.

18:45.920 --> 18:51.360
Simply put, being able to get around more easily increased the amount of land available.

18:51.360 --> 18:53.280
See all this urban sprawl?

18:53.280 --> 18:57.600
That's because of cheaper land out on the fringes of metropolitan areas.

18:57.600 --> 19:02.560
And that's a big reason why Georgism became somewhat obsolete.

19:02.560 --> 19:08.560
Landowners have also been somewhat successful at other reforms to help the poor.

19:08.560 --> 19:14.720
Like welfare, which wouldn't you know it, also helps them out because this also helps

19:14.720 --> 19:16.560
their land value go up.

19:16.560 --> 19:23.840
But here I am on land in 2022, and there's been a renewed interest in Henry George and

19:23.840 --> 19:27.280
Georgism, especially with the younger folks online.

19:29.520 --> 19:30.720
What's up with that?

19:30.720 --> 19:37.120
Well, despite urban sprawl continuing to be a thing, land prices keep rising sharply.

19:37.120 --> 19:44.000
To a point now where many young folks are priced out, stuck as renters, maybe forever.

19:44.000 --> 19:51.520
The dream of owning a home to build up wealth is slowly fading away, so young folks are like,

19:51.520 --> 19:52.240
screw it.

19:52.240 --> 19:56.480
Let's revisit this land value tax idea again.

19:56.480 --> 20:02.000
You might be thinking, well Mr. Beat, if a land value tax is so great, why isn't there

20:02.000 --> 20:04.240
any place in the world that does it?

20:04.240 --> 20:08.880
And my response is, there are places in the world where they do it.

20:08.880 --> 20:14.480
It's not what Henry George envisioned, but variations of a land value tax exist around

20:14.480 --> 20:21.520
the world in places like Estonia, Singapore, Denmark, Taiwan, and even in parts of the United

20:21.520 --> 20:22.320
States.

20:22.320 --> 20:28.640
However, for a land value tax to truly be effective, it must be widespread.

20:28.640 --> 20:33.680
Otherwise, those not having to pay a land value tax will have an even bigger advantage.

20:33.680 --> 20:39.920
And if a land value tax was ever widely implemented, it likely just couldn't happen overnight.

20:39.920 --> 20:45.840
It would be incredibly unfair in the short term to property owners who paid a lot for

20:45.840 --> 20:51.760
their land, as many of them would likely see their land lose its value over time with a

20:51.760 --> 20:53.200
land value tax.

20:53.200 --> 20:58.480
What's fascinating to me is that George's politically isn't left wing or right wing,

20:58.560 --> 21:03.600
